This is the final sprint. These three features turn your application from a "fun project" into a stable, commercial software product.

Here are the implementation prompts for the Crash Shield, Auto-Updater, and Freemium Model.

1. The Crash Shield (Sentry.io)
This is priority #1. You cannot launch a paid product that vanishes silently when it errors.

Prerequisite: You need to pip install sentry-sdk.

Copy and paste this prompt:

"I need to implement a Crash Shield using Sentry.io to catch errors and show a friendly popup.

1. Setup (main.py):

Import sentry_sdk.

Initialize it at the very start of the app: sentry_sdk.init(dsn='YOUR_DSN_HERE', traces_sample_rate=1.0)

Add a placeholder DSN string for now.

2. The Crash Popup (bug_reporter.py):

Create a function show_crash_popup(exception).

It should open a Red Theme CTkToplevel window.

Title: 'Whoops! SunoSync Crashed'.

Body: 'We encountered an error. A report has been automatically sent to the developer.'

Details: A scrolling textbox showing the traceback (readonly).

Buttons: 'Restart App' and 'Close'.

3. Global Exception Hook:

In main.py, create a function handle_exception(exc_type, exc_value, exc_traceback).

Logic:

Log the error to Sentry: sentry_sdk.capture_exception(exc_value).

Launch the show_crash_popup (must use .after if called from a thread to ensure it runs on the main GUI thread).

Bind this to sys.excepthook."

2. The Auto-Updater
This ensures you can fix bugs after launch without losing users.

Copy and paste this prompt:

"I need to add an Auto-Update Checker. Please create a new file updater.py.

1. The Version Check:

Define a constant CURRENT_VERSION = '1.0.0'.

Create a function check_for_updates().

Logic: Fetch a raw JSON file from my GitHub (e.g., https://raw.githubusercontent.com/User/Repo/main/version.json).

JSON Structure: {'latest_version': '1.0.1', 'download_url': '...'}.

Compare latest_version with CURRENT_VERSION.

2. The UI Notification:

If an update is found, return the data to main.py.

In suno_layout.py, add a 'Update Available' Bar at the very top of the window (Green background).

Text: 'New version v1.0.1 available!'.

Button: 'Download' (opens the URL in the default browser).

3. Threading:

Run this check in a background thread on startup so it doesn't freeze the app launch."

3. The Freemium Model (The Paywall)
Now we lock the doors. We need to track daily usage and block features if the user isn't "Pro."

Copy and paste this prompt:

"I need to implement the Freemium Limits. Please modify config_manager.py and downloader_tab.py.

1. Usage Tracking (config_manager.py):

Add tracking for daily_downloads (int) and last_download_date (string).

Create a method check_limit():

If last_download_date != today, reset daily_downloads to 0.

If is_pro_user() is True, return True (Allowed).

If daily_downloads < 50, return True.

Else, return False (Limit Reached).

Create a method increment_count(): Increases daily_downloads by 1.

2. Enforcing the Limit (downloader_tab.py):

inside the download loop, before downloading a song:

Call config.check_limit().

If False, stop the loop and show a popup: 'Daily Limit Reached (50/50). Upgrade to Pro for unlimited access.'

If True, download and call config.increment_count().

3. Locking the Radio:

In radio_tab.py, check is_pro_user() when the 'Go Live' button is clicked.

If False, show a popup: 'Suno On-Air is a Pro feature.'"

